Politics
========

Running a service like Blot means I must make decisions that are political. To certain extent, I feel like all businesses are political entities, with their own politics. To pretend otherwise is thoughtless. However, I try to operate with a political footprint that is as small as possible: I'm not going to make company policy on say the subject of transubstantiation and I won't accomodate activism on it in the workplace.

With that said, here are my thoughts on a few political issues that directly affect the quotidien operations of Blot: